{"id":8515,"date":"2017-03-17T22:34:13","date_gmt":"2017-03-18T04:34:13","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/?p=8515"},"modified":"2018-12-08T12:30:13","modified_gmt":"2018-12-08T19:30:13","slug":"small-succulent-garden-birds-butterflies","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/small-succulent-garden-birds-butterflies\/","title":{"rendered":"Small Succulent Garden for the Birds and Butterflies"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-0 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-1\"><p><em>This small space succulent garden from Cindy Davison of The Succulent Perch is incredible! You don't have to have a lot of space to have an amazing succulent garden.\u00a0<\/em><\/p>\n<p>On a trip to San Diego I had the pleasure of being invited to visit Cindy Davison's (of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/TheSucculentPerch\/\" target=\"_blank\">The Succulent Perch<\/a>) garden.<\/p>\n<p>I've always admired Cindy's succulent creations and was fortunate enough to have her create some for my book,<em> <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/2iBz6zK\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\">Idiot's Guide: Succulents<\/a><\/em>. When I heard about her garden redesign and saw her pictures of it, I knew I wanted to see it in person.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-8532 size-large\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/I-am-in-love-with-this-small-succulent-garden-So-many-good-ideas-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"I am in love with this small succulent garden! So many good ideas!\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/I-am-in-love-with-this-small-succulent-garden-So-many-good-ideas-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/I-am-in-love-with-this-small-succulent-garden-So-many-good-ideas-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/I-am-in-love-with-this-small-succulent-garden-So-many-good-ideas-585x877.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/I-am-in-love-with-this-small-succulent-garden-So-many-good-ideas-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/I-am-in-love-with-this-small-succulent-garden-So-many-good-ideas.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>So often the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/inspiring-succulent-garden\/\">much admired succulent gardens are massive<\/a> and require a dedicated gardener (or two, or three&#8230;) to maintain.<\/p>\n<h4>However, Cindy's garden is so practical and well designed, and completely awe inspiring. It's not huge but it's so beautiful!<\/h4>\n<p>So, enough of my rambling, you're ready to see it for yourself, right?<\/p>\n<p>The front of her house has beautiful beds overflowing with succulents. It's very inviting. Plus, right off the bat you start to see signs of Cindy's fascination with birds. Notice the birdbath full of succulents to add more height to the succulent display.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8534\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Make-the-most-of-your-small-garden-with-birdbaths-and-succulents-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Make the most of your small garden with birdbaths and succulents\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Make-the-most-of-your-small-garden-with-birdbaths-and-succulents-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Make-the-most-of-your-small-garden-with-birdbaths-and-succulents-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Make-the-most-of-your-small-garden-with-birdbaths-and-succulents-585x877.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Make-the-most-of-your-small-garden-with-birdbaths-and-succulents-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Make-the-most-of-your-small-garden-with-birdbaths-and-succulents.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>She also created a beautiful hanging planter using cork board and greening pins to attach the succulents and then filled in the rest of the space with sphagnum moss. The driftwood and large Echeveria &#8216;Sahara's make for a stunning focal point.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8520\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-vertical-succulent-planter-is-amazing-I-love-the-driftwood-as-the-focal-point-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"This vertical succulent planter is amazing! I love the driftwood as the focal point\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-vertical-succulent-planter-is-amazing-I-love-the-driftwood-as-the-focal-point-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-vertical-succulent-planter-is-amazing-I-love-the-driftwood-as-the-focal-point-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-vertical-succulent-planter-is-amazing-I-love-the-driftwood-as-the-focal-point-585x877.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-vertical-succulent-planter-is-amazing-I-love-the-driftwood-as-the-focal-point-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-vertical-succulent-planter-is-amazing-I-love-the-driftwood-as-the-focal-point.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>When you first enter the side yard you're greeted by this trickling fountain and terra cotta pot of succulents. You'll notice that contrasting colors are used throughout the garden. Here, reds and oranges are complimented with blues and greens.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8537\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-blues-and-greens-in-terra-cotta-pots-to-add-contras-and-interest-to-your-succulent-arrangements-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Plant blues and greens in terra cotta pots to add contras and interest to your succulent arrangements\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-blues-and-greens-in-terra-cotta-pots-to-add-contras-and-interest-to-your-succulent-arrangements-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-blues-and-greens-in-terra-cotta-pots-to-add-contras-and-interest-to-your-succulent-arrangements-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-blues-and-greens-in-terra-cotta-pots-to-add-contras-and-interest-to-your-succulent-arrangements-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-blues-and-greens-in-terra-cotta-pots-to-add-contras-and-interest-to-your-succulent-arrangements-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-blues-and-greens-in-terra-cotta-pots-to-add-contras-and-interest-to-your-succulent-arrangements.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<h4>I love how much thought goes in to every part of Cindy's designs.<\/h4>\n<p>She is very aware of how colors work together, how to make the size of everything feel balanced and proprotioned, and finishes off with perfect accents.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8523\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-complementary-colors-to-add-striking-contrast-in-your-succulent-garden-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Use complementary colors to add striking contrast in your succulent garden\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-complementary-colors-to-add-striking-contrast-in-your-succulent-garden-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-complementary-colors-to-add-striking-contrast-in-your-succulent-garden-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-complementary-colors-to-add-striking-contrast-in-your-succulent-garden-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-complementary-colors-to-add-striking-contrast-in-your-succulent-garden-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-complementary-colors-to-add-striking-contrast-in-your-succulent-garden.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>These cacti are planted in pots and then placed in the ground to keep them small and contained. It's like having a small arrangement but with the pot hidden it blends in nicely with the surrounding landscape.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8533\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Keep-cactus-small-by-planting-them-in-plastic-pots-and-burrying-them-in-soil-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Keep cactus small by planting them in plastic pots and burrying them in soil\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Keep-cactus-small-by-planting-them-in-plastic-pots-and-burrying-them-in-soil-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Keep-cactus-small-by-planting-them-in-plastic-pots-and-burrying-them-in-soil-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Keep-cactus-small-by-planting-them-in-plastic-pots-and-burrying-them-in-soil-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Keep-cactus-small-by-planting-them-in-plastic-pots-and-burrying-them-in-soil-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Keep-cactus-small-by-planting-them-in-plastic-pots-and-burrying-them-in-soil.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The wood planter boxes are all surrounded with succulents, especially by the corners so you don't get too close and bump into them.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8538\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-around-your-grow-boxes-to-add-visual-interest-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Plant succulents around your grow boxes to add visual interest\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-around-your-grow-boxes-to-add-visual-interest-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-around-your-grow-boxes-to-add-visual-interest-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-around-your-grow-boxes-to-add-visual-interest-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-around-your-grow-boxes-to-add-visual-interest-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-around-your-grow-boxes-to-add-visual-interest.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8539\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-near-the-corners-of-grow-boxes-to-prevent-bumping-into-them-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Plant succulents near the corners of grow boxes to prevent bumping into them\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-near-the-corners-of-grow-boxes-to-prevent-bumping-into-them-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-near-the-corners-of-grow-boxes-to-prevent-bumping-into-them-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-near-the-corners-of-grow-boxes-to-prevent-bumping-into-them-585x877.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-near-the-corners-of-grow-boxes-to-prevent-bumping-into-them-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Plant-succulents-near-the-corners-of-grow-boxes-to-prevent-bumping-into-them.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Cindy is also great at keeping things natural and organic and has included a grow box full of greens that can easily be picked and eaten. The &#8220;trellis&#8221; here is actually a table with the legs removed and turned on it's side. Genius!<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8519\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-trellis-is-actually-a-table-without-legs-turned-on-its-side-585x390.jpg\" alt=\"This trellis is actually a table without legs turned on its side\" width=\"585\" height=\"390\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-trellis-is-actually-a-table-without-legs-turned-on-its-side-250x167.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-trellis-is-actually-a-table-without-legs-turned-on-its-side-500x333.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-trellis-is-actually-a-table-without-legs-turned-on-its-side-585x390.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-trellis-is-actually-a-table-without-legs-turned-on-its-side-700x467.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/This-trellis-is-actually-a-table-without-legs-turned-on-its-side.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<h4>Really, everything about this garden is adorable.<\/h4>\n<p>She has included little hints of birds and butterflies every where, some large and obvious but some more subtle, like a treasure hunt.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8536\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Nestle-small-garden-trinkets-in-between-plants-for-a-fun-visual-surprise-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Nestle small garden trinkets in between plants for a fun visual surprise\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Nestle-small-garden-trinkets-in-between-plants-for-a-fun-visual-surprise-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Nestle-small-garden-trinkets-in-between-plants-for-a-fun-visual-surprise-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Nestle-small-garden-trinkets-in-between-plants-for-a-fun-visual-surprise-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Nestle-small-garden-trinkets-in-between-plants-for-a-fun-visual-surprise-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Nestle-small-garden-trinkets-in-between-plants-for-a-fun-visual-surprise.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8535\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Miniature-birdhouses-can-be-added-to-any-garden-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Miniature birdhouses can be added to any garden\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Miniature-birdhouses-can-be-added-to-any-garden-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Miniature-birdhouses-can-be-added-to-any-garden-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Miniature-birdhouses-can-be-added-to-any-garden-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Miniature-birdhouses-can-be-added-to-any-garden-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Miniature-birdhouses-can-be-added-to-any-garden.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8526\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-small-birdhouses-throughout-your-garden-to-add-unity-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Add small birdhouses throughout your garden to add unity\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-small-birdhouses-throughout-your-garden-to-add-unity-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-small-birdhouses-throughout-your-garden-to-add-unity-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-small-birdhouses-throughout-your-garden-to-add-unity-585x877.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-small-birdhouses-throughout-your-garden-to-add-unity-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-small-birdhouses-throughout-your-garden-to-add-unity.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8528\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Creating-a-theme-within-your-succulent-garden-is-a-great-way-to-add-unity-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Creating a theme within your succulent garden is a great way to add unity\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Creating-a-theme-within-your-succulent-garden-is-a-great-way-to-add-unity-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Creating-a-theme-within-your-succulent-garden-is-a-great-way-to-add-unity-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Creating-a-theme-within-your-succulent-garden-is-a-great-way-to-add-unity-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Creating-a-theme-within-your-succulent-garden-is-a-great-way-to-add-unity-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Creating-a-theme-within-your-succulent-garden-is-a-great-way-to-add-unity.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>And if all the birdhouses, bird baths and miniatures aren't enough, she even has a cute &#8220;trash can&#8221; that doubles as decor. I've been on a lookout for something as fun as this wood pail, but haven't found anything yet.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8521\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-a-painted-wood-pail-as-a-trash-can-and-decor-in-your-succulent-garden-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Use a painted wood pail as a trash can and decor in your succulent garden\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-a-painted-wood-pail-as-a-trash-can-and-decor-in-your-succulent-garden-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-a-painted-wood-pail-as-a-trash-can-and-decor-in-your-succulent-garden-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-a-painted-wood-pail-as-a-trash-can-and-decor-in-your-succulent-garden-585x877.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-a-painted-wood-pail-as-a-trash-can-and-decor-in-your-succulent-garden-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-a-painted-wood-pail-as-a-trash-can-and-decor-in-your-succulent-garden.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>It's hard to really show you the scale of this garden, but it's not big. Two people can walk down the path at the same time, but there's not a lot of extra space.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8527\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/An-arbor-adds-visual-interest-to-a-succulent-garden-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"An arbor adds visual interest to a succulent garden\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/An-arbor-adds-visual-interest-to-a-succulent-garden-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/An-arbor-adds-visual-interest-to-a-succulent-garden-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/An-arbor-adds-visual-interest-to-a-succulent-garden-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/An-arbor-adds-visual-interest-to-a-succulent-garden-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/An-arbor-adds-visual-interest-to-a-succulent-garden.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8522\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-an-arbor-to-create-a-window-into-your-succulent-garden-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Use an arbor to create a window into your succulent garden\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-an-arbor-to-create-a-window-into-your-succulent-garden-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-an-arbor-to-create-a-window-into-your-succulent-garden-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-an-arbor-to-create-a-window-into-your-succulent-garden-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-an-arbor-to-create-a-window-into-your-succulent-garden-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Use-an-arbor-to-create-a-window-into-your-succulent-garden.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I think that's one (of many) things that makes her garden resonate so well with me.<\/p>\n<h4>It's very simple\u00a0and doable for anyone!<\/h4>\n<p>Those of us window sill and porch gardeners wouldn't need much more space to create something like this.<\/p>\n<p>I love the addition of the chimenea so you can enjoy a fresh cooked meal while sitting among your plants.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8530\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Enjoy-outdoor-cooking-in-your-succulent-garden-with-a-chimenea-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Enjoy outdoor cooking in your succulent garden with a chimenea\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Enjoy-outdoor-cooking-in-your-succulent-garden-with-a-chimenea-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Enjoy-outdoor-cooking-in-your-succulent-garden-with-a-chimenea-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Enjoy-outdoor-cooking-in-your-succulent-garden-with-a-chimenea-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Enjoy-outdoor-cooking-in-your-succulent-garden-with-a-chimenea-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Enjoy-outdoor-cooking-in-your-succulent-garden-with-a-chimenea.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The plant choice for the garden definitely features succulents, but Cindy has also included plants that will attract birds, bees and butterflies, like this milkweed. Though we didn't see any at the time, there were some Monarch cocoons hanging on nearby succulents.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8525\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-milkweed-to-your-succulent-garden-to-attract-butterflies-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Add milkweed to your succulent garden to attract butterflies\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-milkweed-to-your-succulent-garden-to-attract-butterflies-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-milkweed-to-your-succulent-garden-to-attract-butterflies-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-milkweed-to-your-succulent-garden-to-attract-butterflies-585x877.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-milkweed-to-your-succulent-garden-to-attract-butterflies-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Add-milkweed-to-your-succulent-garden-to-attract-butterflies.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>While the plants are stunning, and definitely the most exciting feature of the garden, I am also a bit obsessed with the way Cindy used gravel to add more visual interest within the garden.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8517\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Stunning-Echeveria-Sahara-with-Crassula-lycopoides-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Stunning Echeveria Sahara with Crassula lycopoides\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Stunning-Echeveria-Sahara-with-Crassula-lycopoides-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Stunning-Echeveria-Sahara-with-Crassula-lycopoides-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Stunning-Echeveria-Sahara-with-Crassula-lycopoides-585x877.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Stunning-Echeveria-Sahara-with-Crassula-lycopoides-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Stunning-Echeveria-Sahara-with-Crassula-lycopoides.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>She used three different sizes of gravel in the same color family. Larger right around the succulents, medium sized just out from that, and then the majority was the size of coarse sand. It's like having a matted picture, but in your garden.<\/p>\n<p>Speaking of pictures&#8230; Cindy has a large photo hanging on the side of her house, just above the air conditioning unit. Rather than try to hide the unit she embraced it and decorated around it.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8540\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Rather-than-hide-your-AC-unit-just-hang-a-photo-above-it-to-add-a-different-focal-point-and-surround-it-with-succulents-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Rather than hide your AC unit just hang a photo above it to add a different focal point and surround it with succulents\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Rather-than-hide-your-AC-unit-just-hang-a-photo-above-it-to-add-a-different-focal-point-and-surround-it-with-succulents-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Rather-than-hide-your-AC-unit-just-hang-a-photo-above-it-to-add-a-different-focal-point-and-surround-it-with-succulents-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Rather-than-hide-your-AC-unit-just-hang-a-photo-above-it-to-add-a-different-focal-point-and-surround-it-with-succulents-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Rather-than-hide-your-AC-unit-just-hang-a-photo-above-it-to-add-a-different-focal-point-and-surround-it-with-succulents-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Rather-than-hide-your-AC-unit-just-hang-a-photo-above-it-to-add-a-different-focal-point-and-surround-it-with-succulents.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<h4>The large picture is so fun and make the garden feel like an extension of the house.<\/h4>\n<p>She has also decorated the air conditioner with a succulent arrangement, just like you would a table inside!<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8529\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Decorate-your-AC-unit-by-adding-a-succulent-arrangement-instead-of-hiding-it-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Decorate your AC unit by adding a succulent arrangement instead of hiding it\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Decorate-your-AC-unit-by-adding-a-succulent-arrangement-instead-of-hiding-it-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Decorate-your-AC-unit-by-adding-a-succulent-arrangement-instead-of-hiding-it-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Decorate-your-AC-unit-by-adding-a-succulent-arrangement-instead-of-hiding-it-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Decorate-your-AC-unit-by-adding-a-succulent-arrangement-instead-of-hiding-it-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Decorate-your-AC-unit-by-adding-a-succulent-arrangement-instead-of-hiding-it.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>One of my consistently favorite succulents (I have a lot and it really depends on the day) is Sedum clavatum. As I was photographing this beauty, Cindy told me this was her very first succulent! It's amazing how one plant can completely change your life&#8230;<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8541\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Sedum-clavatum-hanging-out-of-a-terra-cotta-pot-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"Sedum clavatum hanging out of a terra cotta pot\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Sedum-clavatum-hanging-out-of-a-terra-cotta-pot-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Sedum-clavatum-hanging-out-of-a-terra-cotta-pot-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Sedum-clavatum-hanging-out-of-a-terra-cotta-pot-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Sedum-clavatum-hanging-out-of-a-terra-cotta-pot-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/Sedum-clavatum-hanging-out-of-a-terra-cotta-pot.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I left Cindy's garden feeling so uplifted and inspired! I can't wait to do something like this in my future home. It gave\u00a0me some ideas for how to spruce up any apartment or home we rent, so I'll be sure to show you those one I do them.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-8524\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/A-stunning-Mangave-Bloodspoot-succulent-585x878.jpg\" alt=\"A stunning Mangave Bloodspoot succulent\" width=\"585\" height=\"878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/A-stunning-Mangave-Bloodspoot-succulent-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/A-stunning-Mangave-Bloodspoot-succulent-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/A-stunning-Mangave-Bloodspoot-succulent-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/A-stunning-Mangave-Bloodspoot-succulent-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/A-stunning-Mangave-Bloodspoot-succulent.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>If you want to see more of Cindy's beautiful work, check out my book, <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/2iBz6zK\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\"><em>Idiot's Guides: Succulents<\/em><\/a> or head over to her <a href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/TheSucculentPerch\/\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook page<\/a> where she shares photos of her arrangements and design tips for creating your own.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-2 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-1 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-2\"><p><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":7,"featured_media":9169,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[46,71,1],"tags":[81],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/8515"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/7"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href